   "source": [
    "# Eikonale Explorer — Path Planning via Eikonal Equation\n",
    "\n",
    "**Auteurs** : KpihX & Pacifique000  \n",
    "**Date** : TP7 Refactoring - 2026\n",
    "\n",
    "## Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "Ce notebook explore la résolution de l'équation Eikonale pour la planification de chemin (Path Planning).\n",
    "Contrairement aux approches par échantillonnage (RRT*) ou par essaims (PSO), cette méthode repose sur la propagation d'un front d'onde modélisé par l'équation aux dérivées partielles (EDP) :\n",
    "\n",
    "674307 |\nabla \phi(x)| = N(x) 674307\n",
    "\n",
    "où :\n",
    "- $\phi(x)$ est la fonction de coût (temps d'arrivée ou distance pondérée) depuis la source.\n",
    "- (x)$ est l'indice de réfraction (inverse de la vitesse locale). =1$ dans le vide,  \gg 1$ dans les obstacles.\n",
    "\n",
    "Le chemin optimal est ensuite reconstruit en suivant la direction de descente du gradient de $\phi$ :\n",
    "\n",
    "674307 \frac{d\mathbf{x}}{dt} = -\frac{\nabla \phi}{|\nabla \phi|} 674307"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "# Import du package refactorisé\n",
    "from eikonale_explorer.environment import Environment\n",
    "from eikonale_explorer.solvers import LaxFriedrichsSolver\n",
    "from eikonale_explorer.path_finder import PathFinder\n",
    "\n",
    "# Configuration d'affichage\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (10, 8)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Chargement de l'environnement\n",
    "\n",
    "Nous utilisons les mêmes fichiers de scénario que pour le projet ."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "SCENARIO_FILE = \"data/scenario0.txt\"\n",
    "\n",
    "env = Environment(SCENARIO_FILE)\n",
    "env.plot(title=f\"Environnement: {SCENARIO_FILE}\", show=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Résolution de l'Équation Eikonale (Lax-Friedrichs)\n",
    "\n",
    "Nous utilisons le schéma numérique de **Lax-Friedrichs** pour trouver la solution de viscosité de l'équation Eikonale stationnaire.\n",
    "\n",
    "Le schéma itératif est :\n",
    "\n",
    "674307 \phi_{i,j}^{n+1} = \frac{1}{4}(\phi_{i+1,j} + \phi_{i-1,j} + \phi_{i,j+1} + \phi_{i,j-1}) - \Delta t \cdot H(\nabla \phi_{i,j}, N_{i,j}) 674307\n",
    "\n",
    "Nous discrétisons l'espace avec une grille  \times N_y$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Paramètres de discrétisation\n",
    "GRID_SIZE = 128\n",
    "h = env.width / GRID_SIZE\n",
    "nx = int(env.width / h)\n",
    "ny = int(env.height / h)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Grille: {nx}x{ny}, pas h={h:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Génération de la carte d'indices (Coût)\n",
    "# N=1 (vide), N=100 (obstacle)\n",
    "N_map = env.get_refractive_index_map(nx, ny, base_index=1.0, obstacle_index=50.0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Résolution\n",
    "solver = LaxFriedrichsSolver(max_iter=3000, tol=1e-5)\n",
    "phi = solver.solve(N_map, env.start, h, show_progress=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualisation du champ de potentiel phi\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "env.plot(ax=ax, show=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Affichage des contours\n",
    "x = np.linspace(0, env.width, nx)\n",
    "y = np.linspace(0, env.height, ny)\n",
    "X, Y = np.meshgrid(x, y)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Masquer les valeurs dans les obstacles pour une meilleure lisibilité\n",
    "phi_masked = np.ma.masked_where(N_map > 10, phi)\n",
    "\n",
    "cs = ax.contour(X, Y, phi_masked, levels=40, cmap='viridis', alpha=0.6)\n",
    "plt.colorbar(cs, label='Temps/Coût')\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Champ Eikonal (Isochrones)\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Reconstruction de Chemin (Gradient Descent)\n",
    "\n",
    "Une fois le champ $\phi$ calculé (représentant le \"coût\" pour atteindre chaque point depuis le départ), le chemin optimal depuis l'arrivée est trouvé en remontant le gradient : on suit la pente la plus raide vers la source (où $\phi=0$).\n",
    "\n",
    "Nous comparons deux méthodes d'intégration EDO :\n",
    "1. **Euler Explicite** (Ordre 1)\n",
    "2. **Heun** (Runge-Kutta 2, Ordre 2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Reconstruction avec HEUN (plus précis)\n",
    "path_heun = PathFinder.solve_heun(phi, env.start, env.goal, h)\n",
    "print(f\"Chemin Heun: {len(path_heun)} points\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Reconstruction avec EULER (plus simple)\n",
    "path_euler = PathFinder.solve_euler(phi, N_map, env.start, env.goal, h)\n",
    "print(f\"Chemin Euler: {len(path_euler)} points\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Comparaison Graphique\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))\n",
    "env.plot(ax=ax, show=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.contour(X, Y, phi_masked, levels=20, cmap='gray', alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "if len(path_euler) > 0:\n",
    "    ax.plot(path_euler[:, 0], path_euler[:, 1], 'r--', label='Euler', linewidth=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "if len(path_heun) > 0:\n",
    "    ax.plot(path_heun[:, 0], path_heun[:, 1], 'b-', label='Heun (Optimal)', linewidth=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Reconstruction de Chemin : Euler vs Heun\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Tests sur tous les scénarios\n",
    "\n",
    "Boucle automatique sur les fichiers disponibles dans ."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import glob\n",
    "\n",
    "scenarios = sorted(glob.glob(\"data/scenario*.txt\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "for scen_file in scenarios:\n",
    "    print(f\"Processing {scen_file}...\")\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        # Pipeline complet\n",
    "        e = Environment(scen_file)\n",
    "        n_x_sub = int(e.width / (e.width/100)) # Approx grid size 100\n",
    "        h_sub = e.width / n_x_sub\n",
    "        n_y_sub = int(e.height / h_sub)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        nm = e.get_refractive_index_map(n_x_sub, n_y_sub, obstacle_index=50.0)\n",
    "        s = LaxFriedrichsSolver(max_iter=2000, tol=1e-4)\n",
    "        p_field = s.solve(nm, e.start, h_sub, show_progress=False)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        path = PathFinder.solve_heun(p_field, e.start, e.goal, h_sub)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Plot rapide\n",
    "        fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))\n",
    "        e.plot(ax=ax, show=False, title=Path(scen_file).name)\n",
    "        ax.plot(path[:, 0], path[:, 1], 'b-', lw=2)\n",
    "        plt.show()\n",
    "        \n",
    "    except Exception as err:\n",
    "        print(f\"Error on {scen_file}: {err}\")"
   ]
  }
 ],
